#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:5 8ea1ea6f82d446a2a5bd9216b97ed9c0
msgid "OpenVPN Road Warrior"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:8 e204a017bdb842779edcc56c23640dee
msgid ""
"Road Warrior refers to a specific configuration of the OpenVPN VPN "
"tailored for remote users, allowing them secure access to a private "
"network from anywhere on the internet. This setup is particularly useful "
"for businesses and organizations with employees or collaborators spread "
"across different locations, ensuring encrypted communication and data "
"privacy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:13 2f9939d2db1d4b26b935f1b240e07586
msgid ""
"OpenVPN is a protocol supported by the most widely used platforms, with "
":ref:`free clients <client_software-section>` available for Windows, "
"MacOS, Linux, Android, and iOS systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:15 49264337d8e64102b00945662162fe4a
msgid ""
"Before configuring the OpenVPN Road Warrior, make sure you have read the "
"chapter related to the :ref:`user database <users_database-section>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:18 4adebce533754590a13e95577b895c84
msgid "Server configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:20 31aa2a2730824c01b0c36c5e6fd7c399
msgid ""
"An OpenVPN server is running on NethSecurity waiting for remote clients "
"to contact it and establish a connection. It must be reachable from the "
"internet on its specific port (default: 1194 UDP). Multiple clients can "
"connect to the server, authenticate themselves and gain access to the "
"private network; however, the clients do not need to be reachable on the "
"internet. Each connecting client, after authentication, receives an IP "
"address with which it will present itself to the remote network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:23 5ee0e288502e4051afc289c4bbdd79b2
msgid ""
"An OpenVPN server on NethSecurity is closely tied to a user database, "
"which can be local or remote. The association with the database is "
"defined during server creation and cannot be modified later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:26 167923b4fce749af83ead8f62318560f
msgid ""
"The server configuration is straightforward because NethSecurity "
"automatically sets most fields to sane defaults, which usually only need "
"verification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:28 b4529b67d23345c895471f438beb43aa
msgid ""
"To configure a new OpenVPN server, click :guilabel:`Create Server` button"
" and configure the proposed fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:30 9d7908fadcec42519b7da7cd81e1765b
msgid "``Server name``: give a name to this OpenVPN server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:32 c10e66baee7c4a1784b976b5ca993e2d
msgid ""
"``User database``: choose the user database to use for authentication, it"
" can be a local database or a remote one (e.g. LDAP or Active Directory)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:34 3dd901bd13174d6994fbd2c198e7b369
msgid ""
"``Create an account for each user``: this is a special field and won't be"
" shown again in the future, it allows you to automatically create a VPN "
"account for each user present in the database. All accounts created will "
"have a certificate valid for 3650 days."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:36 f4207f81164d411c88c97cadf60ae693
msgid ""
"``Mode``: bridged or routed; routed mode is the default one and the most "
"common, it allows to create a virtual network where clients are connected"
" to the server and can communicate with each other. Bridged mode is less "
"common and allows to connect the clients to the server as if they were "
"connected to the same LAN this mode is useful when the clients need to "
"access resources that are not directly accessible from the server. If "
"unsure, select routed mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:42 434161d5b96a4f0ebf41bb92bdbed78c
msgid "``Authentication mode``: several authentication modes are supported:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:44 86c436490166433db98752da440ce5a4
msgid ""
"``Username and password``: the connecting client must provide a valid "
"username and password; only users with a password set can use this mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:46 46fb41f74d124fb5aad22a7dbac97c8c
msgid ""
"``Certificate``: the connecting client must have its own certificate to "
"authenticate; this is the recommended mode for most cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:48 690052b46dc8438495aabf034bbd5101
msgid ""
"``Username password and certificate``: the connecting client must provide"
" a valid username, password and certificate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:50 12b45166eb374607b93a5bca84844766
msgid ""
"``Username OTP and certificate``: the connecting client must provide a "
"valid username, certificate and also an OTP code used as a password. This"
" mode requires additional configuration in the client to receive to OTP "
"code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:52 6ec47655d8c34bd99ee665a00665753a
msgid ""
"``VPN Network``: the virtual network used by clients; every client will "
"receive an IP address taken from this network. NethSecurity already "
"suggests an uncommon network to avoid overlaps with other networks used "
"by the firewall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:54 cf3440d9463144768ab8bc160080147a
msgid ""
"``Dynamic range IP start``: the first IP address that will be assigned to"
" clients connecting to the server; the address must be part of the VPN "
"network. When adding an IP reservation to client, make sure that the IP "
"address is outside the dynamic range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:57 30b2177aec0d47b19a382e001bb7b775
msgid ""
"``Dynamic range IP end``: the last IP address that will be assigned to "
"clients connecting to the server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:59 897dd4295cd64ad7adeb0675d6a71776
msgid ""
"``Public IP/hostname of this unit``: NethSecurity automatically fills out"
" this field with the public IP address of each configured WAN interface. "
"These IPs/hostnames will go into the client configuration. The order of "
"the elements is crucial because the connecting client will start "
"contacting the IPs/hostnames beginning with the first in the list and "
"then progressing down the list in case of unavailability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:63 8eef5018d4a14deebf00d9e6622b16aa
msgid ""
"Click on the :guilabel:`Create` button to create the server. After that, "
"main server details will be shown in the Web UI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:66 66335d1b7b124215a8233fdb5be1da49
msgid "Advanced settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:68 9ff8643f95f443a080fb3a5d7cc45ffb
msgid "If needed, you can also customize some advanced options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:70 9922a3c6f35942cb80fd3383f450cbbd
msgid "``Protocol``: UDP (default), TCP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:72 391d9cabefdb43379237607e8bba016a
msgid "``Port``: 1194 (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:74 b0dda460200843d2aee5e978e19ef745
msgid ""
"``Route all client traffic through VPN``: if enabled, all traffic from "
"the client will be routed into the VPN tunnel, even standard internet "
"traffic. It can be used for monitoring and control purposes, but is "
"typically disabled because it introduces increased latency and consumes "
"bandwidth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:76 36b981cfaeeb46d08e63663507585c77
msgid ""
"``Push network routes``: a list of networks that the client should route "
"in the VPN tunnel; the LAN networks are automatically added, but they can"
" also be removed and other networks can be added in the same way"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:78 8427dd1649974b35ba3a41a963a0cf8e
msgid ""
"``Allow client-to-client network traffic``: allows all connected clients "
"to exchange traffic between them; it is recommended to leave it disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:80 4add49cfc718482eb4900bc482aa89bd
msgid ""
"``Compression``: compress the OpenVPN tunnel traffic to save bandwidth. "
"However, it is now a less useful option and, in some cases, can be "
"detrimental. It is highly recommended to leave it disabled. When this "
"option is modified, it is necessary to download the client configuration "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:82 afc1cae22ca24e2584ce6661c3c118d9
msgid ""
"``Digest``: the digest authenticates data channel packets (default SHA "
"256)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:84 6d9de19595b14e0bb885bc676d0bf36e
msgid "``Cipher``: encryption cipher used (default AES-256-GCM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:86 0695316caa3d4f0db4999dd9b056ed4e
msgid ""
"``Enforce a minimum TLS version``: allows connection only for clients "
"using a TLS version equal to or greater than the one specified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:88 e7427741e7d542608c905b0f77e75b0b
msgid ""
"``Custom DHCP options``: pass specific DHCP options to the client (e.g. "
"DOMAIN, DNS, WINS and so on)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:92 56cea6464dae45a2bc705a9e8393009c
msgid "DHCP options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:94 96f5cb5b35224258b1910b934c550bb8
msgid ""
"The DHCP options are used to pass specific configuration parameters to "
"the client. Available DHCP options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:97 6715a26129e340359bcef6ff34a28778
msgid ""
"``DNS [addr]``: set primary and secondary DNS server addresses (IPv4 or "
"IPv6). Repeat the option to set multiple addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:99 dd5201523f754d689e7b36f9689e13dc
msgid ""
"``WINS [addr]``: set primary and secondary Windows Internet Name Service "
"Server (NetBIOS over TCP/IP Name Server) addresses. Repeat the option to "
"set multiple addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:102 3f3a4e44ef304780beedb5cd5df91f34
msgid ""
"3. ``NBDD [addr]``: set primary and secondary NetBIOS Datagram "
"Distribution Server (NetBIOS over TCP/IP Datagram Distribution Server) "
"addresses. Repeat the option to set multiple addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:105 3c5d279c59a942df8c71a391b91b2ca4
msgid ""
"``NTP [addr]``: set primary and secondary Network Time Protocol server "
"addresses. Repeat the option to set multiple addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:107 e5ddb5e425764b5680f5bae02493d35b
msgid "``NBT [type]``: set NetBIOS over TCP/IP ode type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:109 b200fd349a6647149d350b69a2dce3c3
msgid "``1``: Broadcast"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:110 cf242e8afc584c058f6b85f3eb2d0203
msgid "``2``: Point-to-point (uses WINS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:111 922ebe2a7b9f486cbc229766ee540207
msgid "``4``: Mixed (broadcast, then query name server)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:112 2097d126d9a44e33b7b768e7e14da887
msgid "``8``: Hybrid (query name server, then broadcast)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:114 b90163c35d044d3e8b5eb2bdee03abf3
msgid ""
"``NBS [scope-id]``: set NetBIOS Scope ID to isolate NetBIOS traffic and "
"allow unique computer names across different scopes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:116 196ef2a0b6604cebb57d50c716990e30
msgid ""
"``DISABLE-NBT [1]``: Turn off NetBIOS over TCP/IP. The parameter is "
"simply ``1`` to enable the option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:119 68336fe4af7341979f499282053dadef
msgid "VPN accounts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:121 25105bd1652f4d22849efb75f846d8d1
msgid ""
"Now that the server has been configured, it is necessary to create the "
"accounts for the connecting clients. To do this, click on :guilabel:`Add "
"VPN Account` and fill out the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:123 ec1db0cd69cb4e59beea9d9b0da9b4be
msgid ""
"``User``: each account is associated with only one user from the chosen "
"database, select the user for this account"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:125 03476a3461af44bfa57a466b4a31d340
msgid ""
"``Reserved IP``: specify an IP address that is part of the defined VPN "
"network but outside the dynamic range. The entered IP address will always"
" be assigned to this specific account, this can be very useful for "
"creating firewall rules. Leave it blank to assign a random IP address on "
"every connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:129 3f0d94a722d24277bdf8e3ef7ab7095e
msgid ""
"``Certificate expiration (days)``: specify a certificate duration "
"(default 3650 days)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:131 0c46e876141c44d19432c64d98c15ef5
msgid ""
"Once the account is created, it is necessary to export the configuration "
"and load it into the client that needs to connect. To do this, simply "
"click on the menu of the specific account and choose ``Download "
"configuration``. This action downloads the ready-to-use file, simply to "
"be loaded into the client. This file is dynamically generated based on "
"the current configuration of the OpenVPN server and already contains all "
"the necessary information, including configuration details (server "
"addresses, port, etc.) and required certificates. In case the server's "
"operating mode is changed (e.g., if the authentication mode is altered), "
"it is necessary to download the file again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:134 f086f6adcd294b9ca90cd59075c14706
msgid "Other available actions are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:136 d4d4c5ce007f4300afe4f6f097c1b996
msgid ""
"``Disable``: disable the account; the account can be re-enabled at any "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:138 df698dbf66424f65a51ada6e75fc54e7
msgid ""
"If a client is already connected to the roadwarrior server, the "
"``Disable`` action on the respective account causes an immediate "
"disconnection from the server, interrupting the communication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:140 43c5100aff0d4e88b00771d2162ef58f
msgid ""
"``Regenerate certificate``: recreate the personal certificate for the "
"account; if the current certificate has not expired, it will be revoked, "
"and it will be necessary to use the new one. After recreating the "
"certificate, it is necessary to update it on the client by either re-"
"downloading the entire configuration or just the certificate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:142 90ef06efb9a144b881ff58554ba22fcd
msgid ""
"``Delete``: delete the account and its certificate, this operation is "
"irreversible and the certificate is not recoverable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:145 3017c14068a94fb3b4f9f1a80e3bb540
msgid "Client behavior"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:147 0f6fbcb45d3f489eb91c323cb98f0d6c
msgid "Some information about the behavior of the clients:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:149 ccafb79850284e64af65e4b015ffe9eb
msgid ""
"Clients connected to the Road Warrior VPN are assigned to the "
"``rwopenvpn`` zone, which is inherently trusted. By default, this zone "
"has privileged access to both LAN and WAN zones within the network "
"infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:152 d514c1995f9c4fb3880cd2040fb368f2
msgid ""
"Connection backup: in case of multiple WANs, clients will connect using "
"the first IP/hostname of the server configuration, if it's unavailable "
"they will use the second IP/hostname and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:154 36b7a91661fd4877970000140e0bd4c7
msgid ""
"For security reasons, it is not possible to connect multiple clients with"
" the same account. Each account can be used by only one client at a time."
" If a new client attempts to connect with an account that is already "
"connected to the system, the first account will be disconnected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:161 0261c79c916e434dab2196a042c26c97
msgid "Client software"
msgstr ""

#: ../../openvpn_roadwarrior.rst:163 da0691413e37425cb8b20e94001654fc
msgid ""
"All major platforms are supported. Here are some references to download "
"the necessary software:"
msgstr ""

